result.name: FRITES Belgium on Tap

reviews.text: Absolutely loved our dining experience at Fries. Had a fantastic evening meal after work with our team, the menu is spot on and I couldn't go past the Chicken Parmigiana. It was delicately cooked with the right balance of cheese and sauce and was by far my most satisfying meal of the week. The drinks are great too with something for everyone. Service was impeccable so we came back the following day for lunch.

Good place for lunch but gets crowded quickly. If you are in a rush then it's advisable to book for 11:45. Service and food will be quick at that time. After 12:30 it's difficult to get a spot. The steak is always cooked perfectly and the set lunch is a good deal if you don't mind the smaller range of options.

Very busy over lunch hour, reservation recommended. Lunch set include soup, main, desserts and drink, fine food and good presentation. Waiters are friendly and responsive. Environment is open and comfy, windows allow natural sunlight. A bit too noisy though.

Really nice place - but extremely extremely noisy! It's surprising how many families there are but the bar area is less noisier place to sit in than the table area. 
There actually is a kid's play area next to the dining area so go figure, I guess.

We had the Chicken Frisee Salad and Beef & Frites to share - I could eat both alone too on a lazy day. The food is good and the price/portion is fair although the beef was kinda fatty cut. Fries were quite amazing! 
They also have these huge pots of mussels but didnt try out those as I absolutely hate mussels - they seemed quite popular dish and there was variety
Bit noisy,  pork knuckle skin over cooked.  But the food were great!
